#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.94"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.94:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 10. Saḷavagga → chaḷavaggo (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn35.94:0.2"
msgid "10. Saḷavagga"
msgstr "10. The Sixes"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 94. Adantaaguttasutta → saṃgayha 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.94:0.3"
msgid "94. Adantaaguttasutta"
msgstr "94. Untamed, Unguarded"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.70"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Chayime, bhikkhave, phassāyatanā adantā aguttā arakkhitā asaṃvutā "
"dukkhādhivāhā honti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these six fields of contact bring suffering when they’re "
"untamed, unguarded, unprotected, and unrestrained."

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.3"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.4"
msgid ""
"Cakkhu, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ adantaṃ aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ asaṃvutaṃ "
"dukkhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"The field of eye contact brings suffering when it’s untamed, unguarded, "
"unprotected, and unrestrained."

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.5"
msgid ""
"jivhā, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ adantaṃ aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ asaṃvutaṃ "
"dukkhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"The field of ear contact … nose contact … tongue contact … body contact …"

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.6"
msgid ""
"mano, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ adantaṃ aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ asaṃvutaṃ "
"dukkhādhivāhaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"The field of mind contact brings suffering when it’s untamed, unguarded, "
"unprotected, and unrestrained."

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.7"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha phassāyatanā adantā aguttā arakkhitā asaṃvutā "
"dukkhādhivāhā honti”."
msgstr ""
"These six fields of contact bring suffering when they’re untamed, unguarded, "
"unprotected, and unrestrained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.1"
msgid ""
"Chayime, bhikkhave, phassāyatanā sudantā suguttā surakkhitā susaṃvutā "
"sukhādhivāhā honti."
msgstr ""
"These six fields of contact bring happiness when they’re well tamed, well "
"guarded, well protected, and well restrained."

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.2"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhu, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ sudantaṃ suguttaṃ surakkhitaṃ susaṃvutaṃ "
"sukhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"The field of eye contact brings happiness when it’s well tamed, well "
"guarded, well protected, and well restrained."

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.4"
msgid ""
"jivhā, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ sudantaṃ suguttaṃ surakkhitaṃ susaṃvutaṃ "
"sukhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"The field of ear contact … nose contact … tongue contact … body contact …"

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.5"
msgid ""
"mano, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ sudantaṃ suguttaṃ surakkhitaṃ susaṃvutaṃ "
"sukhādhivāhaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"The field of mind contact brings happiness when it’s well tamed, well "
"guarded, well protected, and well restrained."

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.6"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha phassāyatanā sudantā suguttā surakkhitā susaṃvutā "
"sukhādhivāhā hontī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These six fields of contact bring happiness when they’re well tamed, well "
"guarded, well protected, and well restrained.”"

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.8"
msgid "etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Saḷeva → chaḷeva (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.1"
msgid "“Saḷeva phassāyatanāni bhikkhavo,"
msgstr "“Mendicants, it’s just the six fields of contact"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.2"
msgid "Asaṃvuto yattha dukkhaṃ nigacchati;"
msgstr "that lead the unrestrained to suffering."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.3"
msgid "Tesañca ye saṃvaraṇaṃ avedisuṃ,"
msgstr "Those who understand how to restrain them"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.4"
msgid "Saddhādutiyā viharantānavassutā."
msgstr "live with faith as partner, uncorrupted."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.1"
msgid "Disvāna rūpāni manoramāni,"
msgstr "When you’ve seen pleasant sights"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.2"
msgid "Athopi disvāna amanoramāni;"
msgstr "and unpleasant ones, too,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.3"
msgid "Manorame rāgapathaṃ vinodaye,"
msgstr "get rid of desire for the pleasant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.4"
msgid "Na cāppiyaṃ meti manaṃ padosaye."
msgstr "without hating what you don’t like."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.71"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.1"
msgid "Saddañca sutvā dubhayaṃ piyāppiyaṃ,"
msgstr "When you’ve heard sounds both liked and disliked,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.2"
msgid "Piyamhi sadde na samucchito siyā;"
msgstr "don’t fall under the thrall of sounds you like,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.3"
msgid "Athoppiye dosagataṃ vinodaye,"
msgstr "get rid of hate for the unliked,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.4"
msgid "Na cāppiyaṃ meti manaṃ padosaye."
msgstr "and don’t hurt your mind by thinking of what you don’t like."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.1"
msgid "Gandhañca ghatvā surabhiṃ manoramaṃ,"
msgstr "When you’ve smelled a pleasant, fragrant scent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.2"
msgid "Athopi ghatvā asuciṃ akantiyaṃ;"
msgstr "and one that’s foul and unpleasant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.3"
msgid "Akantiyasmiṃ paṭighaṃ vinodaye,"
msgstr "get rid of aversion for the unpleasant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.4"
msgid "Chandānunīto na ca kantiye siyā."
msgstr "while not yielding to desire for the pleasant."

# Following PTS reading: … bhotva saditan ca sadun ca
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.1"
msgid "Rasañca bhotvāna asāditañca sāduṃ,"
msgstr "When you’ve enjoyed a sweet, delicious taste,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.2"
msgid "Athopi bhotvāna asādumekadā;"
msgstr "and sometimes those that are bitter,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.3"
msgid "Sāduṃ rasaṃ nājjhosāya bhuñje,"
msgstr "don’t be attached to enjoying sweet tastes,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.4"
msgid "Virodhamāsādusu nopadaṃsaye."
msgstr "and don’t despise the bitter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
#. VAR: majje → majjhe (si, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.1"
msgid "Phassena phuṭṭho na sukhena majje,"
msgstr "Don’t be intoxicated by a pleasant touch,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.2"
msgid "Dukkhena phuṭṭhopi na sampavedhe;"
msgstr "and don’t tremble at a painful touch."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.3"
msgid "Phassadvayaṃ sukhadukkhe upekkhe,"
msgstr "Look with equanimity at the duality of pleasant and painful contacts,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.4"
msgid "Anānuruddho aviruddha kenaci."
msgstr "without favoring or opposing anything."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.1"
msgid "Papañcasaññā itarītarā narā,"
msgstr "People generally let their perceptions proliferate;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.2"
msgid "Papañcayantā upayanti saññino;"
msgstr "perceiving and proliferating, they are attracted."

# For manomaya here, compare thag 21.1, which has Sabbaso gehasitañca vitakkaṃ;
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.3"
msgid "Manomayaṃ gehasitañca sabbaṃ,"
msgstr "When you’ve dispelled all thoughts of the lay life,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.4"
msgid "Panujja nekkhammasitaṃ irīyati."
msgstr "wander intent on renunciation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ mano chassu yadā subhāvito,"
msgstr "When the mind is well developed like this regarding the six,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.2"
msgid "Phuṭṭhassa cittaṃ na vikampate kvaci;"
msgstr "it doesn’t waver at contacts at all."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.3"
msgid "Te rāgadose abhibhuyya bhikkhavo,"
msgstr "Mendicants, those who have mastered greed and hate"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Bhavattha → bhavātha (bj) | bhavatha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.4"
msgid "Bhavattha jātimaraṇassa pāragā”ti."
msgstr "go beyond birth and death.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
